paragraphs:
[17]
In order "to induce or procure another person to infringe an intellectual property right", one must do something that leads that other person to infringe the intellectual property right, or must:
(a) knowingly;
(b) induce or procure (for example, by offering for sale, and knowing that their use by the purchaser would be an infringement);
(c) another to infringe the intellectual property right.
( <FRAGMENT_SUPPRESSED>  (F.C.A.) and  <FRAGMENT_SUPPRESSED>  at 83 (Ex. Ct.).)
